The list you have linked is a variant of Valakut decks that some call Makeshift 
It is a lot more than other variants as it is trying as hard as possible to turboramp into a Primeval Titan and try to cheat all sorts of things into play by ramping and casting Through the Breach or Trap 
The more common variant of Valakut decks is called Scapeshift which plays like a control deck 
A set of Remands and Cryptic Commands let you slow your opponent game plan down while you accelerate your mana to cast Scapeshift with lands in play 
I say this variant is the most consistent and competitive as it can defend itself very well and is rather flexible 
The key reason why the deck is super popular right now is because Pod a great matchup was banned and the Twin decks are no longer as good a matchup as they used to be 
Kolaghan Command can be a serious beating against us 
