Random tips Always float mana when you cast Scapeshift 
This way you leave up interaction after Scapeshift resolves for their bounce or other interaction 
The rule of thumb for damage is that you can deal a maximum of Mountains left in your deck Valakuts you have access to in play or in deck 
Even if you draw a bunch of Mountains keep this rule in mind 
The reason I have never played BUG not even before Become Immense became popular is this You do need Plague Stinger and the other black cards are better than the cost of playing them 
Right now I rather play Sylvan Scrying than a Stinger because Nexus is a much more resilient threat 
The hurt to your manabase is real in BUG and when the key card you get out of black is at all worth it the splash is worth it 
As for Decay and Thoughtseize the two most common black cards people splash for I dislike those as well 
Discard spells do really have a place in Infect because cheap counters like Dispel Spell Pierce and Spell Snare play the protection role so much better 
Sure they only deal with removal but you do care about much else AND they have to invest mana into their Terminate or Kommand generally more than you spend to counter it 
Decay is certainly a useful and versatile spell but again here I have never wished I had it 
I honestly ca give a good argument against playing it but if it the only card you splashing for you can go without it 
Finally I do like that BUG is a lot slower 
You have extra and proactive discard after board in addition to a manabase which can be difficult to get set up properly in a reasonable timeframe 
