The biggest problem for Scapeshift is decks 
Burn Affinity Zoo and others including very fast combo decks can get you dead before you can properly set up because your interaction does really come online until turns because you spend the early turns ramping 
For this reason sideboards frequently contain sweepers and lifegain such as Thragtusk and Obstinate Baloth as well as cheap counterspells for Burn 
One of the ideas of the sideboard is to turn into a different kind of deck against people who bring in hate cards like Slaughter Games 
Baloth Tusk Inferno Titan etc 
can win games on their own or at least buy you time to get to mana and find your kill 
Another idea is to play a bunch of haymakers 
We get to do that because Scapeshift makes a lot of mana We get to play a lot of really powerful spells ahead of time 
Shatterstorm is the headliner for this plan but even Boseiju and Gigadrowse serve as incredibly difficult to beat endgame spells 
